<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Chris Evans was the butt of every meme over the weekend, following an accidental nude leak.</p>

<p>But the Captain America actor is taking the embarrassing situation with a sense of humor, as well as a sense of duty.</p>

<p>He poked fun at the scandalous moment Monday on Twitter, as he broke his social media silence to urge his fans to vote in the upcoming presidential election on November 3.</p>

<p>Rock the vote: Chris Evans poked fun at his recent accidental nude leak Monday on Twitter, as he broke his social media silence to urge his fans to vote (pictured in April, 2019)</p>

<p>The 39-year-old wrote to his 14million followers: 'Now that I have your attention.... VOTE Nov 3rd!!!'</p>

<p>He previously posted a video Saturday, which ended with a quick glimpse of his camera roll, including a black-and-white photo of someone's penis.</p>

<p>It also featured a handsome photo of Chris, which was meme-ified to read: 'Guard that p***y.' </p>

<p>Chris quickly deleted the video upon realizing his mistake, but not quick enough, as he soon began trending on Twitter. </p>

<p>Scandalous post: He previously posted a video Saturday, which ended with a quick glimpse of his camera roll, including a black-and-white photo of someone's penis (pictured in September, 2019)</p>

<p>Going viral: Chris quickly deleted the video upon realizing his mistake, but not quick enough, as he soon began trending on Twitter (pictured in November, 2019)</p>

<p>The reaction on social media was mostly supportive, while it was also met with good-natured jokes and memes from friends and fans.</p>

<p>Brother Scott Evans, 36, posted: 'Was off social media for the day yesterday. So. What’d I miss?'</p>

<p>Avengers: Endgame costar Mark Ruffalo, 52, wrote: '<?php echo e('@'); ?>ChrisEvans Bro, while Trump is in office there is NOTHING you could possibly do to embarrass yourself. See... silver lining.'</p>

<p>Fellow Marvel actor Kat Dennings, 34, used the opportunity to call out a sexist double standard.</p>

<p>She wrote: 'The public respect for Chris Evans' privacy/feelings is wonderful. Wouldn’t it be nice if it extended to women when this kind of thing happens?' </p>

<p>All in good fun: The reaction on social media was mostly supportive, while it was also met with good-natured jokes and memes from friends and fans</p>
